name: Fundog Hotdog Kabobs
author: Anna F
summary: This recipe started out as a fun conversation at work but it turned out to be a big hit at the BBQ. Garnish with mustard. Serve with Frank's® Kraut.
ingredients: 1 (16 ounce) package hot dogs, cut into bite-size pieces
1  red bell pepper, cut into bite-size pieces
1  green bell pepper, cut into bite-size pieces
directions: Soak skewers in a bowl of water for about 30 minutes; drain
Preheat an outdoor grill for low heat and lightly oil the grate
Thread hot dog pieces, red bell pepper pieces, green bell pepper pieces, onions, pineapple chunks, grape tomatoes, and dill pickles onto the skewers
Grill kabobs on the preheated grill, turning frequently, until lightly browned, about 15 minutes
